import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of CO2 levels over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['CO2'], data['adjusted_CO2'])
    plt.xlabel('CO2')
    plt.ylabel('adjusted_CO2')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between CO2 and adjusted CO2 levels?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.boxplot(data['CO2'])
    median = data['CO2'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Median: {median:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the average CO2 level?")
    plt.xlabel("CO2")
    plt.ylabel("Levels")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    data['Month'] = data['Date'].dt.month
    monthly_data = data.groupby('Month')['CO2'].mean()
    
    plt.plot(monthly_data.index, monthly_data.values)
    
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Levels')
    plt.title('What is the seasonal pattern of CO2 levels?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
